-- Fed Funds Projected to Open at 0.02% to 0.07%, ICAP Says
-- B y   L i z   C a p o   M c C o r m i c k
-- 2011-12-30T12:05:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/fed-funds-projected-to-open-at-0-02-to-0-07-icap-says.html
Fed funds, the U.S. overnight inter-
bank lending  rate (FDFD) , is projected to open in a range of 0.02
percent to 0.07 percent, within the  Federal Reserve ’s target of
zero to 0.25 percent.  Fed funds closed at 0.28 percent yesterday after trading
from 0.04 percent to 0.28 percent and averaging 0.07 percent,
ICAP Plc, the world’s largest inter-dealer broker, said in an e-
mailed statement. ICAP’s monthly average is 0.074 percent.  The Federal Reserve Bank of New York will release its
monthly schedule for its Treasury purchases and sales as part of
its program to replace $400 billion of short-term debt in its
portfolio with longer-term Treasuries to reduce borrowing costs
further and counter risk of a recession.  The announcement is scheduled for 2 p.m. New York time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liz Capo McCormick in  New York  at 
